#all data mentioned below is wrt to linux distro some configuration or steps might change as per OS and arch.(i am using fedora 25)

*-opensource and interpreted langauge

*-python scripts have extension ".py"
> python script_name.py  // to execute the program
else set execute permission and then execute the script.
> chmod +x script.py
> ./script.py


*- at the beginning of the script need to mention the interpreter location
  #!/usr/bin/env python3   // in my case this is the default location. 

*-supports datatypes like
  -list,tuples,dictionary,integer,string,float & etc
  -python is dynamically typed language i.e whatever datatype is added to a variable gets assined to that type, 
    no need to specify data type.
  > type(<variable name>)  // this command is used to specify the datatype of a varible

*- "#" is used for commenting purpose.Interpreter won't interpret the lines marked with # at the begning of the line.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# modules :
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
*-They are ".py" files which acts as an library files.
*-it can be used in any program by using: 
    > import <module name>  or 
    > from <module name> import <sub module name>
    we can use alise for module name > import <module name> as <alise name>
  -some usefull modules are inbuilt that comes with interpreter rest we can 
    install using "pip" installer or https://pypi.python.org/pypi

*-to view module information use dir(<module name>) or help(<module name>)
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Reading input form user
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

*- > input():
    -this function is used to prompt user to input via command line into the program
    -raw_input() was used in python2.x but from python3.x it is deprecated
    
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Numbers     
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
  -interger,long integer,floating-point,octal & hex,complex number.
  > eval( <complex expression> )   // this command is used to evaluate the complex expression.
  
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------  
#Typecast
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------    
 *- changing the datatype form one type to another.
  <data type>( <variable name> ) eg int(data)   // it will convert datatype of data variable into integer.
  -int(),float(),str() & etc

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# formatting strings
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
 *- {n} this are placeholders the list inside .format() will replace {n} as per index
 > print(" i m {0},i love {1}".format("vishal","python"))


*- divmod(x,y) // this function will divide x/y and it returns (quotient, remainder)

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
#if - else conditional statement
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
*-if <statement> :
    -condition check statement,if the mentioned condiditon is satisifed then the program control will enter into the block for  execution else exit the condition check.
*-else:
    - when 'if' statement fails the condition check then by defualt this block gets executed
*-elif <statement> :
    -this is 'else if' block gets to check condition if 'if' fails
 program can have many 'if' or 'elif' but only one 'else'
 
 --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 #while loop
 --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 *- while( <conditional statement> ):
    -untill the conditional statement is true the block of code will execute the code
 *- break
    -this is the keyword that is used to break the execution loop.
  
  
 
 
  
